Would you like to contribute to more accessibel and affordable healthcare worldwide? read below how you can contribute as a drug safety specialist!
Omschrijving
As drug safety specialist you're responsibilities will be based on your experience and knowledge of the regulatory standards and guidelines. Activities will mostly be focused around overseeing compliance activities such as performing pharmacovigilance audits and managing agreements regarding pharmacovigilance. Other activities will focus around managing third party supplier quality by writing safety documentation, coordinating updates and processing data.
Aanbod
As drug safety specialist you'll receive a starting salary between 3935 and 4700 a month;
You'll receive fringe benefits, including a budget inclusief een budget om jouw thuiswerkplek in te richten;
The option to work from home two days a week;
The option to work 32 hours a week;
An employer that was acknowledged in 2017 and 2019 as a great place to work!
bedrijfsprofiel
The organisational goal is to create more accessible an affordable healthcare around the world. By optimizing production processes and continuously improving drug quality, they aim to reduce the cost of healthcare around the world. As drug safety specialist you'll become a part of the drug safety team, a small and close knit group of 10 employees, with different levels of experience en responsibilities. Given the responsibilities of the team include managing safety and quality in satellite facilities around the world and getting them all on the same level, you'll be in constant cooperation with your colleagues.
Eisen
You're in possession of a masters degree in a relevant discipline like medical biology or bio-pharmaceutical sciences;
You've got experience with pharmacovigilance related activities;
Full professional mastery of the English language, in speech and writing;
Experience as drug safety specialist or similar function is an advantage.
